Bonus questions not covered in book.

Write a class that can get the date of the last modification    // public long lastModified()
can check whether or not you can write to that file             // public boolean canWrite()
and can set a file to read-only.                                // public boolean setReadOnly()
Hint, use the "File" class.

// boolean canWrite() : Tests whether the application can modify the file denoted by this abstract
pathname.